ed: from unknown (HELO gull.mail.pas.earthlink.net) (207.217.120.84)\n  by mta1.grp.scd.yahoo.com with SMTP; 30 Jul 2004 02:33:24 -0000\r\nReceived: from h-67-101-38-2.snfccasy.dynamic.covad.net ([67.101.38.2] helo=archive.org)\n\tby gull.mail.pas.earthlink.net with esmtp (Exim 3.33 #1)\n\tid 1BqNCq-00071K-00\n\tfor archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com; Thu, 29 Jul 2004 19:33:13 -0700\r\nMessage-ID: &lt;4109B437.3020304@...&gt;\r\nDate: Thu, 29 Jul 2004 19:36:39 -0700\r\nOrganization: Internet Archive\r\nUser-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.0; en-US; rv:1.6b) Gecko/20031205 Thunderbird/0.4\r\nX-Accept-Language: en-us, en\r\nMIME-Version: 1.0\r\nTo: archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com\r\nContent-Type: text/plain; charset=GB2312\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit\r\nX-eGroups-Remote-IP: 207.217.120.84\r\nFrom: Igor Ranitovic &lt;igor@...&gt;\r\nSubject: Re: [archive-crawler] Re: Limit crawling to Markup?\r\nX-Yahoo-Group-Post: member; u=137477665\r\nX-Yahoo-Profile: iranitovic\r\n\r\nHi Ansi,\n\nAs Tom pointed out the regular expression that I posted is false since I\nincorrectly paste and copy it from the source code.\nSorry for the confusion that I caused.\ni.\n\nzhousp wrote:\n&gt; Igor Ranitovic,���ã�\n&gt; \n&gt; \tI tryed this but still have some .jpg and .gif file in the ARC file. please see the attachment.\n&gt; this is the order.xml I use.\n&gt; \n&gt; ansi\n&gt; \n&gt; ======= 2004-07-28 01:50:05 ����������д����=======\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt;&gt;Hi Rob,\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;If you think that filtering out URLs that don&#39;t look like html pages is good enough for your needs \n&gt;&gt;than you can just simple add URIRegExp exclude filter:\n&gt;&gt;^.*(?i)(&#92;&#92;.(bmp|gif|jpe?g|png|tiff|mid|mp2|mp3|mp4|wav|avi|mov|mpeg|ram|rm|smil|wmv|doc|pdf|ppt|swf)$\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Keep in mind that are many URLs out there that are not html pages and don&#39;t end with any generic \n&gt;&gt;suffix. For example:\n&gt;&gt;http://multi1.rmuk.co.uk/RealMedia/ads/adstream_nx.ads/www.pm.gov.uk/homepage@Top!Top\n&gt;&gt;is an image. Without examining HTTP Content-Type header it would be extremely hard to write any \n&gt;&gt;generic URL based filters to exclude these non-html pages.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Take care,\n&gt;&gt;i.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;I guess I&#39;m somewhat confused because I was thinking that the\n&gt;&gt;&gt;additionalScopeFocus filter could be used for something like this,\n&gt;&gt;&gt;basically by having it return false instead of true, which I was\n&gt;&gt;&gt;thinking would cause the URI to be left out of the scope.  Admittedly\n&gt;&gt;&gt;my initial efforts at leaving out images, audio, etc. this way haven&#39;t\n&gt;&gt;&gt;worked, but I hadn&#39;t gotten around to asking about it here.  So, now\n&gt;&gt;&gt;I&#39;m asking.  \n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;Thanks,\n&gt;&gt;&gt;Rob Eger\n&gt;&gt;&gt;Aptas, Inc.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;--- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com, stack &lt;stack@a...&gt; wrote:\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Ahnu Nahki wrote:\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Is there a way to only have heritrix downloaded all text/html markup\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;and disregard altogether images and other binaries. I notice that this\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;eats up alot of time on our crawls.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Thanks,\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Ahnu\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;This topic has been discussed variously here on the list.  You might \n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;check the archive.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;In short, not without doing some work.  Lesser work would be a filter \n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;that skipped non-text/html content after download.  More work would\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;be a \n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;check that interrupted crawls mid-download if the type was other than \n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;what you wanted. \n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Though sub-optimal, you could try and write a regex that only excludes \n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;resources with URIs that match a particular pattern.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;St.Ack\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Yahoo! Groups Links\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt; \n&gt;&gt;&gt;Yahoo! Groups Links\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt; \n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Yahoo! Groups Links\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;.\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =\n&gt; \t\t\t\n&gt; \n&gt; ������������������\n&gt; ��\n&gt;  \n&gt; \t\t\t\t \n&gt; ����������������zhousp\n&gt; ����������������zhousp@...\n&gt; ��������������������2004-07-28\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt;  \n&gt; Yahoo! Groups Links\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt;  \n\n"}}